    feat(11d): post-publish smoke scripts per AC-056
    
    Adds three smoke scripts under scripts/release/smoke/ — the gate that
    proves a published artifact actually installs and runs cleanly on a
    fresh machine, distinct from the CI build which only proves the
    workspace compiles. Per feedback_release_verification: green CI +
    published artifact is NOT done.
    
      smoke-crates-cli.sh:  cargo install fathomdb-cli --version $1
                            → fathomdb doctor check-integrity --json
                            → jq parses output. Engine::open creates the
                            DB file lazily, so no init verb required.
      smoke-pypi-wheel.sh:  fresh venv + pip install fathomdb==$1
                            → Engine.open + write + search + close
                            → python process exits 0.
      smoke-npm-package.sh: fresh npm init + npm install fathomdb@$1
                            → Engine.open + write + search + close
                            → node process exits 0.
    
    Each script: `set -euo pipefail`, semver regex guard on $1 before any
    network call, mktemp -d fixture dir, EXIT trap for cleanup,
    version-pinned install command.
    
    Test coverage in scripts/tests/test_smoke_scripts.sh is STRUCTURAL,
    not integration — running real installs against real registries would
    need network, the artifact existing at the test version, and tens of
    seconds of wall time per script. Header comment documents the
    rationale. Wired into agent-test.sh.
    
    Owner: dev/design/release.md § Post-publish smoke.

