commit c044edb43951d5e5874d03bc7e9e83891f5e28ca
Author: Corey Thompson <coreyt@gmail.com>
Date:   Sun May 17 10:16:47 2026 -0500

    fix(11d): version pins for in-workspace deps + set-version coverage
    
    Blocker surfaced by `cargo publish --dry-run -p fathomdb-engine`:
    
      error: failed to verify manifest at fathomdb-engine/Cargo.toml
      Caused by: all dependencies must have a version requirement specified
      when publishing. dependency `fathomdb-embedder-api` does not specify a
      version
    
    cargo strips `path = ...` at publish time and resolves siblings through
    the registry, so every in-workspace dep needs a version requirement —
    without it, T4 (engine) and every later tier would fail at actual tag
    time even though local `cargo build` is happy.
    
    Adds [workspace.dependencies] to Cargo.toml with one centralized pin
    per sibling (Axis W for fathomdb / fathomdb-embedder / fathomdb-engine
    / fathomdb-query / fathomdb-schema; Axis E for fathomdb-embedder-api).
    Each crate's `[dependencies]` switches its in-workspace deps to
    `<crate>.workspace = true`, so the version flows from one source.
    
    scripts/set-version.sh:
      --workspace <v>     now also rewrites every Axis-W
                          [workspace.dependencies] pin to <v>.
      --embedder-api <v>  now also rewrites the Axis-E
                          [workspace.dependencies] pin to <v>.
      --check-files       gains a per-pin axis-match check with the same
                          `<file>:<line>: version drift — observed/expected`
                          diagnostic shape as the other checks.
    
    scripts/tests/test_set_version.sh: +3 tests covering the new behaviors
    (drift on a pin, --embedder-api propagation to the Axis-E pin,
    --workspace propagation across every Axis-W pin while leaving Axis E
    alone).
    
    `bash scripts/set-version.sh --check-files` is clean on the new state.

