    feat(11d): restore .github/workflows/release.yml with 8-tier publish
    
    Restores the release workflow adapted to the 0.6.0 crate topology
    (7 publishable workspace crates + 2 binding packages) per
    dev/design/release.md § Tiered publish order. Triggered on `push` of
    v* tags or `workflow_dispatch` (dry-run rehearsal — see below).
    
    Job graph:
    
      verify-release      preflight: actionlint + verify-release-gates.sh
                          (tag↔Cargo.toml, set-version --check-files,
                          HEAD-on-main, CHANGELOG section, crate publish
                          metadata).
      build-python        maturin matrix: linux x86_64/aarch64 (manylinux
                          2_28), darwin x86_64/aarch64, win x86_64, py
                          3.10/3.11/3.12. working-directory: src/python.
      build-napi          napi-rs matrix: linux x86_64, darwin
                          x86_64/aarch64, win x86_64. Uses `npm run
                          build:native` so the napi.triples rename to
                          fathomdb.<label>.node lives in one place.
      build-rust          cargo build --release --workspace + cargo
                          package --no-verify on the three leaf crates
                          (fathomdb-embedder-api, fathomdb-schema,
                          fathomdb-query). Dependents are not packaged
                          here — see in-file comment for the rationale
                          carried forward from the pre-0.6.0 source.
      all-builds-passed   cross-ecosystem gate; every build must succeed
                          before any publish runs.
      publish-rust-t1..t7 strict 8-tier topological publish:
                            T1 fathomdb-embedder-api  (leaf, Axis E)
                            T2 fathomdb-schema        (leaf)
                            T3 fathomdb-query         (leaf)
                            T4 fathomdb-engine        (needs T1+T2+T3)
                            T5 fathomdb-embedder      (needs T1, ordered
                                                       on T4 for index-
                                                       propagation cadence)
                            T6 fathomdb               (facade, needs T4)
                            T7 fathomdb-cli          (needs T6 per
                                                       ADR-0.6.0-crate-
                                                       topology 2026-05-11)
                          Each tier sleeps 60s afterward for crates.io
                          index propagation.
      publish-pypi        Tier 8a, parallel with T5..T7 (gated on T4
                          since PyPI wraps engine via PyO3).
                          pypa/gh-action-pypi-publish with OIDC env.
      publish-npm         Tier 8b, parallel with T5..T7 (gated on T4
                          via napi-rs). npm OIDC trusted publishing
                          via npx npm@latest publish --provenance
                          --access public. working-directory: src/ts.
      post-publish-smoke  AC-056 gate: 3-leg matrix runs scripts/release/
                          smoke/smoke-{crates-cli,pypi-wheel,npm-package}.sh
                          against the version-pinned published artifacts
                          on fresh runners.
      co-tagging-assert   AC-052 gate: scripts/release/assert-co-tagging.sh
                          verifies the sibling triple is published.
      github-release      AC-054 partial: only this job marks the release
                          done. Requires post-publish-smoke +
                          co-tagging-assert to pass, so a failed smoke
                          leaves the release unmarked.
    
    workflow_dispatch dry-run mode (Item 4):
      inputs.dry_run defaults to true; when on:
        * cargo publish steps use --dry-run.
        * pypa/gh-action-pypi-publish points at https://test.pypi.org/
          legacy/.
        * npm publish runs with --dry-run.
        * post-publish-smoke, co-tagging-assert, github-release are
          skipped (they assume real publishes happened).
        * verify-release-gates.sh is skipped (no v* tag context on a
          dispatch trigger; the gate would always fail).
    
    All third-party actions pinned to commit SHAs (H-5 convention,
    shared with ci.yml). actionlint .github/workflows/*.yml passes.

