`workflow_dispatch` exposes `dry_run`, but `verify-release` skips `scripts/verify-release-gates.sh` on every dispatch run, not just rehearsals. If someone dispatches with `dry_run: false`, the workflow can reach real cargo publish, real PyPI publish, real npm publish, post-publish smoke, co-tagging assert, and `github-release` without the tag/main/changelog/version gate ever running. That is a release-path correctness blocker.

